<TITLE> Body of Bangladeshi found with hand severed in Kulala Lumpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka May 16 (bdnews24.com)A Bangladeshi man was found dead on the sidewalk of a restaurant in Taman Sri Sentosa, Jalan Klang Lama, in Kuala Lumpur on Saturday morning with a stab wound on his body and his left hand severed. The victim, known as Nurul Amir, 39, was lying in a pool of blood when found by the restaurant's owner when he was opening it for business at 7.20am Malaysian time, Bernama news agency reported. Brickfields police chief ACP Wan Abdul Bari Wan Abdul Talib said the severed arm which was cut off from the elbow was found about 50 metres away. "We believe the victim was attacked at the side of a road in Taman Sri Sentosa, but managed to run before collapsing in front of the restaurant," he said when contacted by Bernama here. The body was sent to the Universiti Malaya Medical Centre
